Class RunMatching

  • java.lang.Object

    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.RootPaneContainer, javax.swing.WindowConstants

    public class RunMatching
extends javax.swing.JDialog
    This class defines the view to start the process of creation of the final datasets. The status of the process is showed and it can be cancelled by the user.

      • calculateWeightsAndNearestGeopoints

        private static java.lang.Double[][] calculateWeightsAndNearestGeopoints(double[] latitudesNorth,
                                                                        double[] longitudesEast,
                                                                        double buoyLatitudeNorth,
                                                                        double buoyLongitudeEast,
                                                                        int numGeopoints)
        Calculates nearest geopoints and weights depending on distance between buoy and each geopoint (latitude,longitude) in reanalysis data file, nearest geopoints to the buoy will have the highest weights (more importance) and vice versa.
        Parameters:
        latitudesNorth - Array with latitude of each geopoint.
        longitudesEast - Array with longitude of each geopoint.
        buoyLatitudeNorth - Latitude North of the buoy.
        buoyLongitudeEast - Longitude East of the buoy.
        numGeopoints - Number of geopoints to considerer.
        Returns:
        Two dimensional array with indexes of nearest geopoints and weights depending on distance.
